HEADWORD: off-duty
<hw>off-duty</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>not performing or available for
duties at the given moment; <as>as, an <ex>off-duty</ex> policeman</as>.
Opposite of <ant>on-duty</ant>, <ant>working</ant>, and
<ant>on-the-job</ant>.</def> <mark>[prenominal]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> off duty(predicate).</syn>⟦br⟧
